<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Bacon" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Bacon,</orth> hog's flesh pickled: <cit><quote>hang-hog is Latin for b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.1.50" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 1, 50</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a gammon of b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.1.26" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 1, 26</bibl></cit>. Term for a fat person: <cit><quote>on, --s, on!</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.2.95" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 2, 95</bibl></cit>.

